title: For Sale:  Diamondback DB9, lightest, smallest 9mm available
postcontent: Hello everyone, I have a Diamondback DB9 for sale.  Good condition, 2-6rd mags, talon grips.  These guns are the lightest and smallest 9mm available.  The company had some trouble with these when they first came out, but it looks like they have worked out the bugs.  These are super easy to conceal and fairly accurate despite the size.  They can be a handful and are more for advanced users, not a first gun.  Full disclosure:  on round 197 the trigger spring broke.  I was firing factory new Remington 9mm JHP at the time, but 2 rounds of the magazine felt "hot" and it was on the second "hot" round that the issue occurred.  I cannot say for certain that the round was loaded to higher pressure, but it did feel like it.  These guns are designed to work with .124 gr or .115 gr and no +P.  In any event, Diamondback fixed it in a few weeks and I put it through its paces upon return.  The first week back I put 500 rounds down range and it went without a hitch.  I have another DB9 that I carry and it is up to 500-600 rounds with no issues.  This gun is a great gun that is about the size and weight of a .380 but with 9mm punch.  It disappears in a pocket and will go places larger guns can't.  Looking to fund other projects, so no trades right now please.  If interested, please call Don, REDACTED.  Please be 21 or older with current gun permit or we can meet at Warrior Arms in Valpo for transfer.  Thanks for looking, and have a great night.
